defs.docs:
Syn is a parsing library for parsing a stream of Rust tokens into a syntax
 tree of Rust source code.

defs.name: token
defs.docs: Tokens representing Rust punctuation, keywords, and delimiters.

defs.docs:
In some positions, types may not contain the `+` character, to
 disambiguate them. For example in the expression `1 as T`, T may not
 contain a `+` character.

defs.name: parse_mod_style

defs.docs:
Determines whether this is a path of length 1 equal to the given

defs.name: buffer
defs.docs:
A stably addressed token buffer supporting efficient traversal based on a
 cheaply copyable cursor.

defs.name: TokenBuffer
defs.docs:
A buffer that can be efficiently traversed multiple times, unlike
 `TokenStream` which requires a deep copy in order to traverse more than
 once.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Creates a `TokenBuffer` containing all the tokens from the input
 `TokenStream`.

defs.name: new2
defs.docs:
Creates a `TokenBuffer` containing all the tokens from the input
 `TokenStream`.

defs.name: begin
defs.docs:
Creates a cursor referencing the first token in the buffer and able to
 traverse until the end of the buffer.

defs.name: Cursor
defs.docs: A cheaply copyable cursor into a `TokenBuffer`.

defs.name: empty
defs.docs: Creates a cursor referencing a static empty TokenStream.

defs.name: eof
defs.docs:
Checks whether the cursor is currently pointing at the end of its valid
 scope.

defs.name: group
defs.value: fn (mut self, delim: Delimiter) -> Option<(Cursor<'a>, Span, Cursor<'a>)>
defs.docs:
If the cursor is pointing at a `Group` with the given delimiter, returns
 a cursor into that group and one pointing to the next `TokenTree`.

defs.name: ident
defs.docs:
If the cursor is pointing at a `Ident`, returns it along with a cursor
 pointing at the next `TokenTree`.

defs.name: punct
defs.docs:
If the cursor is pointing at an `Punct`, returns it along with a cursor
 pointing at the next `TokenTree`.

defs.name: literal
defs.docs:
If the cursor is pointing at a `Literal`, return it along with a cursor
 pointing at the next `TokenTree`.

defs.name: lifetime
defs.docs:
If the cursor is pointing at a `Lifetime`, returns it along with a
 cursor pointing at the next `TokenTree`.

defs.name: token_stream
defs.docs:
Copies all remaining tokens visible from this cursor into a
 `TokenStream`.

defs.name: token_tree
defs.docs:
If the cursor is pointing at a `TokenTree`, returns it along with a
 cursor pointing at the next `TokenTree`.

defs.name: span
defs.docs:
Returns the `Span` of the current token, or `Span::call_site()` if this
 cursor points to eof.

defs.name: ext
defs.docs: Extension traits to provide parsing methods on foreign types.

defs.name: IdentExt
defs.docs: Additional parsing methods for `Ident`.

defs.name: parse_any
defs.docs: Parses any identifier including keywords.

defs.name: punctuated
defs.docs: A punctuated sequence of syntax tree nodes separated by punctuation.

defs.name: Punctuated
defs.docs:
A punctuated sequence of syntax tree nodes of type `T` separated by
 punctuation of type `P`.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates an empty punctuated sequence.

defs.name: is_empty
defs.docs:
Determines whether this punctuated sequence is empty, meaning it
 contains no syntax tree nodes or punctuation.

defs.name: len
defs.docs: Returns the number of syntax tree nodes in this punctuated sequence.

defs.name: first
defs.docs: Borrows the first punctuated pair in this sequence.

defs.name: last
defs.docs: Borrows the last punctuated pair in this sequence.

defs.name: last_mut
defs.docs: Mutably borrows the last punctuated pair in this sequence.

defs.name: iter
defs.docs: Returns an iterator over borrowed syntax tree nodes of type `&T`.

defs.name: iter_mut
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator over mutably borrowed syntax tree nodes of type
 `&mut T`.

defs.name: pairs
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator over the contents of this sequence as borrowed
 punctuated pairs.

defs.name: pairs_mut
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator over the contents of this sequence as mutably
 borrowed punctuated pairs.

defs.name: into_pairs
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator over the contents of this sequence as owned
 punctuated pairs.

defs.name: push_value
defs.docs:
Appends a syntax tree node onto the end of this punctuated sequence. The
 sequence must previously have a trailing punctuation.

defs.name: push_punct
defs.docs:
Appends a trailing punctuation onto the end of this punctuated sequence.
 The sequence must be non-empty and must not already have trailing
 punctuation.

defs.name: pop
defs.docs:
Removes the last punctuated pair from this sequence, or `None` if the
 sequence is empty.

defs.name: trailing_punct
defs.docs:
Determines whether this punctuated sequence ends with a trailing
 punctuation.

defs.name: empty_or_trailing
defs.docs:
Returns true if either this `Punctuated` is empty, or it has a trailing
 punctuation.

defs.name: push
defs.docs: Appends a syntax tree node onto the end of this punctuated sequence.

defs.name: insert

defs.docs: Inserts an element at position `index`.

defs.name: parse_terminated
defs.docs:
Parses zero or more occurrences of `T` separated by punctuation of type
 `P`, with optional trailing punctuation.

defs.name: parse_terminated_with
defs.value: fn (input: ParseStream, parser: fn(ParseStream) -> Result<T>) -> Result<Self>
defs.docs:
Parses zero or more occurrences of `T` using the given parse function,
 separated by punctuation of type `P`, with optional trailing
 punctuation.

defs.name: parse_separated_nonempty
defs.docs:
Parses one or more occurrences of `T` separated by punctuation of type
 `P`, not accepting trailing punctuation.

defs.name: parse_separated_nonempty_with
defs.value: fn (input: ParseStream, parser: fn(ParseStream) -> Result<T>) -> Result<Self>
defs.docs:
Parses one or more occurrences of `T` using the given parse function,
 separated by punctuation of type `P`, not accepting trailing
 punctuation.

defs.name: Pairs
defs.docs: An iterator over borrowed pairs of type `Pair<&T, &P>`.

defs.name: PairsMut
defs.docs: An iterator over mutably borrowed pairs of type `Pair<&mut T, &mut P>`.

defs.name: IntoPairs
defs.docs: An iterator over owned pairs of type `Pair<T, P>`.

defs.name: IntoIter
defs.docs: An iterator over owned values of type `T`.

defs.name: Iter
defs.docs: An iterator over borrowed values of type `&T`.

defs.name: IterMut
defs.docs: An iterator over mutably borrowed values of type `&mut T`.

defs.name: Pair
defs.docs:
A single syntax tree node of type `T` followed by its trailing punctuation
 of type `P` if any.

defs.name: into_value
defs.docs:
Extracts the syntax tree node from this punctuated pair, discarding the
 following punctuation.

defs.name: value
defs.docs: Borrows the syntax tree node from this punctuated pair.

defs.name: value_mut
defs.docs: Mutably borrows the syntax tree node from this punctuated pair.

defs.name: punct
defs.docs:
Borrows the punctuation from this punctuated pair, unless this pair is
 the final one and there is no trailing punctuation.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Creates a punctuated pair out of a syntax tree node and an optional
 following punctuation.

defs.name: into_tuple
defs.docs:
Produces this punctuated pair as a tuple of syntax tree node and
 optional following punctuation.

defs.name: spanned
defs.docs:
A trait that can provide the `Span` of the complete contents of a syntax
 tree node.

defs.name: Spanned
defs.docs:
A trait that can provide the `Span` of the complete contents of a syntax
 tree node.

defs.name: span
defs.docs:
Returns a `Span` covering the complete contents of this syntax tree
 node, or [`Span::call_site()`] if this node is empty.

defs.name: visit
defs.docs: Syntax tree traversal to walk a shared borrow of a syntax tree.

defs.name: Visit
defs.docs: Syntax tree traversal to walk a shared borrow of a syntax tree.

defs.docs:
Parsing interface implemented by all types that can be parsed in a default
 way from a token stream.

defs.name: ParseBuffer

defs.name: error
defs.docs: Triggers an error at the current position of the parse stream.

defs.docs:
Parses a syntax tree node of type `T`, advancing the position of our
 parse stream past it.

defs.name: call

Calls the given parser function to parse a syntax tree node of type `T`
 from this stream.

defs.name: peek

Looks at the next token in the parse stream to determine whether it
 matches the requested type of token.

defs.docs:
Parses zero or more occurrences of `T` separated by punctuation of type
 `P`, with optional trailing punctuation.

defs.name: is_empty
defs.docs: Returns whether there are tokens remaining in this stream.

defs.name: lookahead1
defs.docs:
Constructs a helper for peeking at the next token in this stream and
 building an error message if it is not one of a set of expected tokens.

defs.name: fork
defs.docs:
Forks a parse stream so that parsing tokens out of either the original
 or the fork does not advance the position of the other.

defs.name: error
defs.docs: Triggers an error at the current position of the parse stream.

defs.name: step
defs.docs:
Speculatively parses tokens from this parse stream, advancing the
 position of this stream only if parsing succeeds.

defs.name: cursor
defs.docs:
Provides low-level access to the token representation underlying this
 parse stream.

 parse stream.
